annotationA: Leucyl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial; aminoacyl-tRNA editing activity; ATP binding; leucine-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: leucyl-tRNA aminoacylation; Belongs to the class-I aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase family
annotationB: Seryl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial (SerRS-m) catalyses the aminoacylation of tRNAser with serine, to be used for gene translation during protein synthesis
